Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.10,0:00:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 2
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.92,0:00:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog and his shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.44,0:00:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A dog once had a nice piece of meat for his dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.24,0:00:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He was walking along with the meat in his mouth as happy as a king
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.10,0:00:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,On his way home, there was a stream
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.06,0:00:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog stopped to look into the calm, clear, water
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.20,0:00:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the dog see in the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.38,0:01:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw a dog looking up at him
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.60,0:01:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This dog looked the same as our happy little dog
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.78,0:01:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And even had a similar piece of meat in its mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.38,0:01:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'll try to get that meat too" said the dog
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.26,0:01:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But as soon as he tried to bite the new piece of meat
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.44,0:01:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,His own meat fell out of his mouth and into the stream
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.66,0:01:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he saw that the other dog in the water had lost his piece too
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.84,0:01:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He went sadly home
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.40,0:01:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That day he only had his dreams to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.84,0:01:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful of losing something you have for something that may not exist
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:01:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,----
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.12,0:02:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Belling the cat
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.61,0:02:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One day all the mice came together to talk about the cat
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.20,0:02:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"We must think of a plan to get away from it" said one old mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.55,0:02:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"It has eaten too many of us, so what shall we do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.19,0:02:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,At last one proud young mouse stood up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.25,0:02:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"You know my brothers" said the young mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.20,0:02:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"The cat movies very quietly, we do not hear it quickly enough to escape"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.63,0:02:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's tie a bell around the cat's neck"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.10,0:02:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Then we can hear it coming and run away"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.12,0:02:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yeah" shouted all the mice
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,"Our smart young friend has thought of an excellent plan"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:03:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's go and buy a bell"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.26,0:03:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But just then an old mouse spoke:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.90,0:03:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Wait a minute" said the wise old mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.38,0:03:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your plan is very good, but who will tie the bell on the cat?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then each mouse looked at another and they all said:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.54,0:03:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Right, who?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.74,0:03:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It is easy to suggest difficult things, but it is hard to do them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.12,0:03:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,----
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.20,0:03:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The hare and the tortoise
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One day a hare was making fun of a tortoise for being so slow
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.88,0:03:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"You think I am slow?" said the tortoise
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:04:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's run a race, and I bet that I will win"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.48,0:04:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh really?" answered the hare "Let's try and see"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.26,0:04:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon the hare and the tortoise agreed that the fox would be the judge for their race
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On race day, both the hare and the tortoise met the fox at the starting line
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.00,0:04:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Both started off together
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.02,0:04:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon the hare was far ahead of the slow tortoise
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.06,0:04:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The hare thought she could stop and take a rest
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.52,0:04:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She found some nice comfortable grass to rest in, and was soon in a deep sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.50,0:04:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile the tortoise kept going and going
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.50,0:04:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He was slow but he never stopped
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.12,0:05:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,After a nice long sleep, the hare woke up
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.80,0:05:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a problem, she slept for too long
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.62,0:05:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She jumped up and ran as fast as she could, but it was too late
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.74,0:05:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The tortoise had already crossed the finish line
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.14,0:05:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Slow and steady wins the race
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.14,0:05:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,----
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Stag at the Lake
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.44,0:05:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One very hot day, a tall strong stag stopped to drink from a clear lake
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.74,0:05:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When he took a drink he could see his image in the water
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.22,0:05:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"My horns are so beautiful" he said
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.46,0:05:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"They're so strong and graceful"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.92,0:06:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"But I'm still sad, because my legs are so thin and ugly"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.82,0:06:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, a lion came through the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And try to jump on the stag
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.44,0:06:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The stag ran away very very fast
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.48,0:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The ugly legs helped him run away
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.34,0:06:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But the lion didn't stop following the stag
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.44,0:06:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon the stag ran into the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But the forest was very thick, with many trees
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.94,0:06:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,His beautiful horns got caught in the branches
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.62,0:06:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He tried to pull away, but he couldn't because of the long horns
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.02,0:06:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally the lion caught up with the stag and killed him
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.16,0:07:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People often forget what is really important in our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,----
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The country mouse and the city mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.18,0:07:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One day a city mouse went to visit his friend in the country
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.20,0:07:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The country mouse was very glad to see his good friend
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He give his guest the best dinner that he could find
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.94,0:07:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The country mouse was afraid that there was not enough food for two
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.30,0:07:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So he just ate a little piece of corn
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.37,0:07:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,His friend had some green peas, a piece of new cheese, and a ripe, red apple
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.63,0:07:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,After the city mouse ate all the dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.48,0:08:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He said "How can you live in the country my friend?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.36,0:08:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"You can see nothing but forest, rivers, fields, and mountains"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"You must be very tired of hearing nothing but bird songs"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.01,0:08:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"Come with me to the city, there you can live in a beautiful house"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.90,0:08:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"And have good things for dinner everyday"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.16,0:08:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"When you have lived in the city for a week"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.61,0:08:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"You will forget all about living in the country"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.30,0:08:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the two mice went to the city
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.59,0:08:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They reached the home of the city mouse at night
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.65,0:08:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"You must be hungry, we walked for a long time"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.70,0:08:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,said the city mouse to his friend
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.03,0:08:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"We will have some dinner immediately"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.38,0:09:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So they went to the dinning room
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.12,0:09:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the city mouse found some cake and fruit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.92,0:09:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Help yourself" he said "There is enough for both of us"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.77,0:09:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"This is a very good dinner" said the country mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.72,0:09:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"You're very rich, my friend"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.30,0:09:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Just then the door opened and the dog came in"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.37,0:09:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The mice jumped off the table, and ran into a hole in the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.75,0:09:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The poor little country mouse was so frightened
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"Do not be afraid" said his friend "the dog cannot come in here"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.34,0:09:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the mice went to the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.41,0:09:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They found an apple pie on the shelf, and were enjoying a piece of it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.54,0:10:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment they saw two bright eyes watching them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.49,0:10:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"The cat! The cat!" cried the city mouse
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mice quickly ran through a hole in the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.01,0:10:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When the country mouse could speak, he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Goodbye my friend, you can live in the city with the dogs and cats"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"I like my home in the country"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"In the country, the birds sing to me, while I eat my simple corn and apples"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.29,0:10:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"In the city, the cats watch you eating your fancy cake, and pie"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.71,0:10:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"I like my corn in safety better than your cake in fear"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.11,0:10:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Better a simple meal in peace, than a fancy meal in fear
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.60,0:11:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The end
